        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 5:22PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 522 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Coleville, moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Topaz Lake, Coleville, Walker, Monitor Pass, Junction U.S 395 And CA
89, Holbrook Junction, and Topaz Lake Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
